Description: Part of a jar-seal: of dark grey clay, with a seal-impression of two names repeated. The clay is fairly well preserved.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXVI, 57; H. R. Hall, 'Catalogue of Egyptian scarabs etc. in the British Museum: Volume 1 : Royal scarabs' (London, 1913), 288, no.2761; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.68, abb.245; see also vols. I, 138 and II, 815, n.800; 1125.
